<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!-- Hymn 4033: Gabriel's Message — C major, 3/4, pickup E
     Pedal harp arrangement: Melody + RH + LH + P (pedal)

     ABC chord analysis (original key Am but lead sheet in C major):
     The melody is clearly in A minor / C major. Chords:
     Am Bm Dm Am | Bø7 Bm | E7 Em7 | Am Bm Dm | Am B° | Am A | Am |
     Am C | G7 C B° | C B° | C e | Dm | D7 | G | G C | Dm Dm7 | Bø7 Dm |
     Bm E | F | Dm7 (with steps) | Am | A | Am | Am

     Diatonic substitutions (C major diatonic: C D E F G A B):
     - Bm → Bø (vii°) — B D F — diatonic in C major
     - Bø7 → viiø7 (B D F A) — diatonic
     - B° → vii° (B D F)
     - E7 → E (iii, just use E G B — non-diatonic dominant, sub iii or V)
     - Em7 → Em (iii)
     - D7 → V7/V area, sub G (V) or use Dm7 (ii7) instead
     - A major → Am (vi) substitute

     Key: C major — NO accid.ges needed for diatonic notes
     Non-diatonic: any F# → accid.ges="s" (from E, A major areas)

     TEXTURE ARC: 3/4 waltz feel
     - Opening: light, 2+3, emphasize A minor color (vi)
     - Middle: build at C major arrivals
     - Climax: measures with e5 melody
     - Close: converge A minor → C major final

     VOICING PLAN:
     - Am area: A-C-E / A-E-A-C (vi "33" / "333")
     - C major area: C-E-G / C-G-C-E (I "33" / "334")
     - V area: G-B-D / G-D-G-B
     - vii° area: B-D-F (dim triad "33")
     - Quartal at phrase openings for color
-->
