<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Gabriel's Message is in A minor (C major key sig, minor tonal center on A).
- vi (Am) treated as tonic: A2-E3-A3 "334" or A2-E3-A3-C4 "333" for stability.
- vii° (Bø/B°) used throughout as leading tone to vi: B2-D3-F3.
- viiø7 for half-dim flavor at longer note values: B2-D3-F3-A3.
- V (G-B-D) used sparingly at dominant arrival points (m7, m16, m22-23).
- I (C-E-G) used at C major arrivals (m15-19) for climax section brightness.
- ii (Dm) for pre-dominant function, also extended as Dm7.
- Pedal bass: A1 at Am, B1 at B°/Bø7, G1 at V, C1 at I.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- Am→vii°: A3 steps down to B3, E3 steps down to D3 (smooth contrary motion).
- vii°→Am: B→A stepwise resolution (leading tone resolution in bass).
- V→I: G2→C2 root motion by P4, smooth voice leading in inner voices.
- The oscillation vi–vii°–vi creates the characteristic brooding modal color of this Basque carol.

TEXTURE ARC:
- m1-13: Spare opening, 2+3 notes, Am modal color. Mostly whole-measure blocks.
- m14-19: I major arrival, 3-note RH adds brightness, C major texture.
- m20-28: Development — Dm7 and viiø7 color, then iii and IV for breadth.
- m29-33: Final cadence section — ii7→vi→vi resolved, sustained final Am.
-->
